1️⃣ DELETE vs TRUNCATE vs DROP
🧠 Mental Model First

Think of a notebook 📓

Operation	Meaning
DELETE	Remove some lines
TRUNCATE	Erase all pages
DROP	Throw away the notebook
🔹 1. DELETE
Simple Idea

👉 Removes specific rows

Example
DELETE FROM students WHERE id = 1;
Features

✔ Can use WHERE
✔ Deletes selected rows
✔ Can be rolled back

Python Connection 🧠
students = [s for s in students if s["id"] != 1]
🔹 2. TRUNCATE
Simple Idea

👉 Removes ALL rows (fast)

Example
TRUNCATE TABLE students;
Features

✔ Removes all data
✔ Very fast
❌ Cannot use WHERE
❌ Cannot rollback (in most DBs)

Mental Model
TRUNCATE = Empty table, keep structure
🔹 3. DROP
Simple Idea

👉 Deletes entire table

Example
DROP TABLE students;
Features

✔ Deletes structure + data
✔ Table is gone completely

🔥 Final Comparison (Very Important)
Feature	DELETE	TRUNCATE	DROP
Removes rows	✅ Yes	✅ All	❌ (removes table)
WHERE allowed	✅ Yes	❌ No	❌ No
Rollback	✅ Yes	❌ No	❌ No
Table exists after	✅ Yes	✅ Yes	❌ No
Memory Trick 🧠
DELETE → selective delete
TRUNCATE → full clear
DROP → remove everything
2️⃣ ALTER & UPDATE

Now let’s learn how to modify data and table structure

🔹 UPDATE (Change Data)
Simple Idea

👉 Used to modify existing data

Example
UPDATE students
SET branch = 'AI'
WHERE id = 1;
Python Connection 🧠
for s in students:
    if s["id"] == 1:
        s["branch"] = "AI"
Important ⚠️

👉 If you forget WHERE:

UPDATE students SET branch='AI';

👉 ALL rows will change 😱

Memory Trick
UPDATE = Change data
🔹 ALTER (Change Table Structure)
Simple Idea

👉 Used to modify table structure

Add Column
ALTER TABLE students
ADD age INT;
Drop Column
ALTER TABLE students
DROP COLUMN age;
Modify Column
ALTER TABLE students
MODIFY name VARCHAR(100);
Python Connection 🧠

Think like modifying structure:

for s in students:
    s["age"] = 20
Memory Trick 🧠
ALTER = Change table structure
🔥 Placement Insight

Very common questions:

Q1: Difference between DELETE and TRUNCATE?

👉

DELETE → row-wise
TRUNCATE → all rows, faster
Q2: Difference between TRUNCATE and DROP?

👉

TRUNCATE → keeps table
DROP → deletes table
Q3: What happens if WHERE is missing in UPDATE?

👉 All rows get updated ❌

Quick Revision (1 Minute)
DELETE → remove some rows
TRUNCATE → remove all rows
DROP → delete table

UPDATE → modify data
ALTER → modify structure
